{"id":"1208.5463","submitter":"Zhora Nikoghosyan","authors":"Zh. G. Nikoghosyan","title":"Nonhamiltonian Graphs with Given Toughness","comments":"11 pages, corrected and improved version","journal-ref":null,"doi":null,"report-no":null,"categories":"math.CO","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  In 1973, Chv\\'{a}tal introduced the concept of toughness $\\tau$ of a graph\nand constructed an infinite class of nonhamiltonian graphs with $\\tau=3/2$.\nLater Thomassen found nonhamiltonian graphs with $\\tau>3/2$, and Enomoto et al.\nconstructed nonhamiltonian graphs with $\\tau=2-\\epsilon$ for each positive\n$\\epsilon$. The last result in this direction is due to Bauer, Broersma and\nVeldman, which states that for each positive $\\epsilon$, there exists a\nnonhamiltonian graph with $\\tau\\ge 9/4-\\epsilon$. In this paper we prove that\nfor each rational number $t$ with $0<t<9/4$, there exists a nonhamiltonian\ngraph with $\\tau=t$.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 27 Aug 2012 18:19:09 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 4 Sep 2012 19:30:39 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Sun, 9 Sep 2012 17:11:31 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Mon, 17 Sep 2012 07:29:02 GMT"}],"update_date":"2012-09-18"}
